579.068. 1. A person commits the offense of trafficking drugs in the second degree
2 if, except as authorized by this chapter or chapter 195, such person knowingly possesses or
3 has under his or her control, purchases or attempts to purchase, or brings into this state:
4 (1) More than thirty grams of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount
5 of heroin;
6 (2) More than one hundred fifty grams of a mixture or substance containing a
7 detectable amount of coca leaves, except coca leaves and extracts of coca leaves from which
8 cocaine, ecgonine, and derivatives of ecgonine or their salts have been removed; cocaine salts
9 and their optical and geometric isomers, and salts of isomers; ecgonine, its derivatives, their
10 salts, isomers, and salts of isomers; or any compound, mixture, or preparation which contains
11 any quantity of any of the foregoing substances;
12 (3) More than five hundred milligrams of a mixture or substance containing a
13 detectable amount of lysergic acid diethylamide (LSD);
14 (4) More than thirty grams of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount
15 of phencyclidine (PCP);
16 (5) More than four grams of phencyclidine;
17 (6) More than thirty kilograms of a mixture or substance containing marijuana;
18 (7) More than thirty grams of any material, compound, mixture, or preparation
19 containing any quantity of the following substances having a stimulant effect on the central
20 nervous system: amphetamine, its salts, optical isomers and salts of its optical isomers;
21 methamphetamine, its salts, optical isomers and salts of its optical isomers; phenmetrazine
22 and its salts; or methylphenidate;
23 (8) More than thirty grams of any material, compound, mixture, or preparation which
24 contains any quantity of 3,4-methylenedioxymethamphetamine; [or]
25 (9) More than [ten] three milligrams of fentanyl [or carfentanil], or any derivative
26 thereof, [or any combination thereof,] or any compound, mixture, or substance containing a
27 detectable amount of fentanyl [or carfentanil], or [their] its optical isomers or analogues; or
28 (10) Any amount of carfentanil.
29 2. The offense of trafficking drugs in the second degree is a class C felony.

HB 1625 5
30 3. The offense of trafficking drugs in the second degree is a class B felony if the
31 quantity involved is:
32 (1) Ninety grams or more of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount of
33 heroin; or
34 (2) Four hundred fifty grams or more of a mixture or substance containing a
35 detectable amount of coca leaves, except coca leaves and extracts of coca leaves from which
36 cocaine, ecgonine, and derivatives of ecgonine or their salts have been removed; cocaine salts
37 and their optical and geometric isomers, and salts of isomers; ecgonine, its derivatives, their
38 salts, isomers, and salts of isomers; or any compound, mixture, or preparation which contains
39 any quantity of any of the foregoing substances; or
40 (3) One gram or more of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount of
41 lysergic acid diethylamide (LSD); or
42 (4) Ninety grams or more of a mixture or substance containing a detectable amount of
43 phencyclidine (PCP); or
44 (5) Twelve grams or more of phencyclidine; or
45 (6) One hundred kilograms or more of a mixture or substance containing marijuana;
46 or
47 (7) More than five hundred marijuana plants; or
48 (8) Ninety grams or more but less than four hundred fifty grams of any material,
49 compound, mixture, or preparation containing any quantity of the following substances
50 having a stimulant effect on the central nervous system: amphetamine, its salts, optical
51 isomers and salts of its optical isomers; methamphetamine, its salts, optical isomers and salts
52 of its optical isomers; phenmetrazine and its salts; or methylphenidate; or
53 (9) Ninety grams or more but less than four hundred fifty grams of any material,
54 compound, mixture, or preparation which contains any quantity of 3,4-
55 methylenedioxymethamphetamine; or
56 (10) [Twenty] Fourteen milligrams or more of fentanyl [or carfentanil], or any
57 derivative thereof, [or any combination thereof,] or any compound, mixture, or substance
58 containing a detectable amount of fentanyl [or carfentanil], or [their] its optical isomers or
59 analogues; or
60 (11) More than five hundredths of a milligram of carfentanil.
61 4. The offense of trafficking drugs in the second degree is a class A felony if the
62 quantity involved is four hundred fifty grams or more of any material, compound, mixture or
63 preparation which contains:
64 (1) Any quantity of the following substances having a stimulant effect on the central
65 nervous system: amphetamine, its salts, optical isomers and salts of its optical isomers;

HB 1625 6
66 methamphetamine, its salts, isomers and salts of its isomers; phenmetrazine and its salts; or
67 methylphenidate; or
68 (2) Any quantity of 3,4-methylenedioxymethamphetamine.
69 5. The offense of drug trafficking in the second degree is a class C felony for the first
70 offense and a class B felony for any second or subsequent offense for the trafficking of less
71 than one gram of flunitrazepam.
